<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="523" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1525,2018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,378,1525,1550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Material examined</emphasis>
. Station 36, holotype (MNCN 16.01/17768) and 11 paratypes (LBUV), plus 2 specimens for SEM (MNCN 16.01/17768). Station 59, 1 paratype (LBUV).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="526" pageId="2" pageNumber="523" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1525,2018]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,464]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="526" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1597,1622]" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[353,457,1597,1622]" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Holotype</typeStatus>
longest complete specimen, a female with developing embryos attached to nephridial pores. Embryos from chaetigers 15 to 40, with developed antennae and anal cirri (
<figureCitation box="[1099,1191,1633,1658]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,211,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1687]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A, complete female with embryos, latero-dorsal view. B, same, anterior end, dorsal view. C, another specimen, dorsal view. D, embryos. E, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. F, Most dorsal compound chaeta, anterior parapodium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065844/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
), attached by anus to nephridial pores. Body long, slender, 
<quantity box="[591,681,1669,1694]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="523" unit="mm" value="5.2">5.2 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[760,864,1670,1694]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="523" unit="mm" value="0.21">0.21 mm</quantity>
wide, 44 chaetigers. Prostomium semicircular to subpentagonal, about 2.5 times wider than long; with four large eyes in trapezoidal arrangement, anterior pair slightly larger than posterior pair; antennae located close to each other, between anterior eyes (
<figureCitation box="[1224,1314,1741,1766]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); antennae all similar, short, ovoid, with median one slightly longer than lateral ones (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1115,1777,1802]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1130,1202,1778,1802]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,211,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1687]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A, complete female with embryos, latero-dorsal view. B, same, anterior end, dorsal view. C, another specimen, dorsal view. D, embryos. E, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. F, Most dorsal compound chaeta, anterior parapodium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065844/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">2B, C</figureCitation>
). Palps broad, fused along their length with distal notch, slightly longer than prostomium (
<figureCitation box="[977,1074,1813,1838]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1092,1167,1814,1838]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,211,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1687]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A, complete female with embryos, latero-dorsal view. B, same, anterior end, dorsal view. C, another specimen, dorsal view. D, embryos. E, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. F, Most dorsal compound chaeta, anterior parapodium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065844/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">2A, C</figureCitation>
). Peristomium distinct; tentacular cirri small, papilliform (
<figureCitation box="[545,640,1849,1874]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[653,725,1850,1874]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,211,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1687]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A, complete female with embryos, latero-dorsal view. B, same, anterior end, dorsal view. C, another specimen, dorsal view. D, embryos. E, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. F, Most dorsal compound chaeta, anterior parapodium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065844/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">2A, C</figureCitation>
). Dorsal cirri longer than tentacular cirri, similar in shape and length to antennae, somewhat smaller on most anterior segments (
<figureCitation box="[954,1054,1885,1910]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1073,1144,1886,1910]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,211,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1687]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A, complete female with embryos, latero-dorsal view. B, same, anterior end, dorsal view. C, another specimen, dorsal view. D, embryos. E, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. F, Most dorsal compound chaeta, anterior parapodium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065844/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">2A–C</figureCitation>
), absent on chaetiger 2. Compound chaetae all short falcigers, with proximal tooth distinctly long and distal tooth small (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1387,1921,1946]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Figs 1C, G, H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1398,1432,1922,1946]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,211,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1687]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A, complete female with embryos, latero-dorsal view. B, same, anterior end, dorsal view. C, another specimen, dorsal view. D, embryos. E, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. F, Most dorsal compound chaeta, anterior parapodium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065844/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">2E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,163,1958,1982]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,511,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,493,1987]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A–C, compound chaetae, midbody. D, Most dorsal compound chaeta and dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta.F, ventral simple chaeta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065846/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">3</figureCitation>
A-D) and short, with straight spines on margin. On median and posterior parapodia, most dorsal compound chaetae with slightly elongated blade and longer spines along margin (
<figureCitation box="[939,1025,1993,2018]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">Figs 1F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1037,1075,1994,2018]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,511,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,493,1987]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A–C, compound chaetae, midbody. D, Most dorsal compound chaeta and dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta.F, ventral simple chaeta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065846/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="523">3D</figureCitation>
). Anterior parapodia each with ca. 8–9 compound chaetae; number of compound chaetae diminishing posteriorly to 4–5 on mid-body and 2–3 on posterior parapodia. Blades of compound chaetae 
<quantity box="[756,842,1837,1861]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long, shorter on posterior parapodia. Dorsalmost compound chaetae of mid-body and posterior parapodia slightly longer, about 
<quantity box="[1072,1197,1873,1897]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" unit="mm" value="12.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="12.0">12–13 mm</quantity>
long. Dorsal simple chaetae from chaetiger 1, with rounded tips and finely spinulose subterminally (
<figureCitation box="[1063,1155,1909,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Figs 1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1169,1206,1909,1933]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,511,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,493,1987]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A–C, compound chaetae, midbody. D, Most dorsal compound chaeta and dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta.F, ventral simple chaeta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065846/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">3D</figureCitation>
), thicker posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[159,274,1945,1970]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Figs 1E, I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[288,323,1945,1969]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,511,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,493,1987]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A–C, compound chaetae, midbody. D, Most dorsal compound chaeta and dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta.F, ventral simple chaeta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065846/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">3E</figureCitation>
). Ventral simple chaetae on posterior parapodia, sigmoid, smooth or with minute subdistal spines, with small distal tooth and longer subdistal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[729,824,1981,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Figs 1K</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[838,870,1981,2005]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,511,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,493,1987]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A–C, compound chaetae, midbody. D, Most dorsal compound chaeta and dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta.F, ventral simple chaeta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065846/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">3F</figureCitation>
). Acicula solitary, distally blunt, becoming larger more posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[355,520,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Figs 1D, H, L</figureCitation>
). Pharynx long, through about 5–6 segments; pharyngeal tooth large, located on anterior rim (
<figureCitation box="[300,389,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[186,1431,227,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Exogone yagan n. sp. MNCN 16.01/17768. Holotype. A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, dorsal simple chaeta, anterior parapodium. C, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. D, acicula, anterior parapodium. E, dorsal simple chaeta, midbody parapodium. F, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. G, acicula, anterior parapodium. H, dorsal simple chaeta, posterior parapodium. I, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. J, ventral simple chaeta, K, acicula, posterior parapodium. Scale bars. A: 0.1 mm.B–K: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065842/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
), surrounded by ten soft papillae. Proventricle similar in length to pharynx, through about 3– 4 segments, with about 20 muscle cell rows. Pygidium with two anal cirri, relatively short in comparison with other related species (
<figureCitation box="[330,420,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1673,1695]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,211,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1687]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Exogone yagan n. sp. SEM. A, complete female with embryos, latero-dorsal view. B, same, anterior end, dorsal view. C, another specimen, dorsal view. D, embryos. E, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. F, Most dorsal compound chaeta, anterior parapodium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1065844/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
