<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="526" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Distribution</emphasis>
. Only known from Chilean Patagonia. Puerto Engaño in Ballenero channel; Magellan Strait to the south. Also Beagle channel southwest arm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,291,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Habitat</emphasis>
. Inside tubes of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Renier" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[481,823,367,392]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chaetopteridae" genus="Chaetopterus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="variopedatus">
<emphasis box="[481,632,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Chaetopterus</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[677,823,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">variopedatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in fjords and channels from Patagonia. Salinity: from 20 to 35 PSU, temperature: from 8.01 to 8.7°C. Shallow subtidal, 
<quantity box="[890,950,404,428]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" unit="m" value="30.0">30 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,829,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,464]" box="[199,829,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,349,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Type locality</emphasis>
. Ballenero channel. Magellan Strait south.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
